  2. Recommended Lakeflow Topology

  Catalogs and Schemas

  ┌─────────┬─────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Catalog │   Schema    │                   Purpose                   │
  ├─────────┼─────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ efence  │ wifi_raw    │ Wi-Fi bronze (append-only, restricted read) │
  ├─────────┼─────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ efence  │ wifi_silver │ Wi-Fi normalized (analyst readable)         │
  ├─────────┼─────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ efence  │ bt_raw      │ BT bronze (append-only, restricted read)    │
  ├─────────┼─────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ efence  │ bt_silver   │ BT normalized (analyst readable)            │
  ├─────────┼─────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ efence  │ gold        │ Shared correlation and alerting outputs     │
  └─────────┴─────────────┴─────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  In dev/stage: use efence_dev / efence_stage catalogs for full isolation.

  Unity Catalog DDL (run once, before first pipeline deploy)

  -- Catalogs (created by admin or via terraform)
  CREATE CATALOG IF NOT EXISTS efence;
  CREATE CATALOG IF NOT EXISTS efence_dev;

  -- Schemas
  CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS efence.wifi_raw;
  CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS efence.wifi_silver;
  CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS efence.bt_raw;
  CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS efence.bt_silver;
  CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS efence.gold;

  -- Volumes for landing zones
  CREATE VOLUME IF NOT EXISTS efence.wifi_raw.landing;
  CREATE VOLUME IF NOT EXISTS efence.bt_raw.landing;

  -- Secret scope (created via CLI)
  -- databricks secrets create-scope efence-secrets
  -- databricks secrets put-secret efence-secrets mac-hash-salt --string-value "..."

  -- ACLs: bronze tables restricted to pipeline service principals only
  GRANT USE SCHEMA ON SCHEMA efence.wifi_raw TO `efence-pipeline-svc`;
  GRANT SELECT ON SCHEMA efence.wifi_raw TO `efence-security-analysts`;
  -- Revoke broad access to bronze (raw MACs)
  REVOKE SELECT ON SCHEMA efence.wifi_raw FROM `account users`;

  -- Silver and Gold readable by analysts
  GRANT SELECT ON SCHEMA efence.wifi_silver TO `efence-analysts`;
  GRANT SELECT ON SCHEMA efence.bt_silver TO `efence-analysts`;
  GRANT SELECT ON SCHEMA efence.gold TO `efence-analysts`;

  Checkpoints

  DLT manages its own checkpoint state under /pipelines/{pipeline_id}/checkpoints/. Do not manually manage these. For Auto Loader specifically, the schema inference location is:
  - Wi-Fi: /Volumes/efence/wifi_raw/_autoloader_schema
  - BT: /Volumes/efence/bt_raw/_autoloader_schema

  These persist across pipeline restarts and are critical — back them up before any forced full-refresh.

  Orchestration Pattern

  Every 5 minutes (Lakeflow Job):
    [wifi-ingest task] ──┐
                         ├──→ [gold-correlation task] → [dq-monitoring task]
    [bt-ingest task]  ──┘

  Daily 02:00 UTC (Lakeflow Job):
    [optimize-wifi-bronze] ──┐
                             ├──→ [vacuum-all] → [daily-dq-report]
    [optimize-bt-bronze]  ──┘

