  4. Ingest Design Decision

  Auto Loader vs. Kafka/Event Hubs

  ┌───────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │         Dimension         │                 Auto Loader (cloudFiles)                 │                     Kafka / Event Hubs                     │
  ├───────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ Latency                   │ Seconds to minutes (depends on trigger interval)         │ Sub-second possible                                        │
  ├───────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ Edge compatibility        │ Pi writes files via HTTPS/SCP/S3 SDK — simple            │ Pi needs Kafka producer client — more complex              │
  ├───────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ Replayability             │ Excellent — raw files persist in landing zone            │ Requires offset management, retention limits               │
  ├───────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ Schema evolution          │ Built-in with schemaEvolutionMode=addNewColumns          │ Manual schema registry (Confluent/AWS Glue)                │
  ├───────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ Backfill                  │ Drop files into landing, pipeline picks up automatically │ Replay from Kafka offset only while retained               │
  ├───────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ Operational complexity    │ Low — no Kafka cluster to maintain                       │ High — Kafka/Event Hubs SLA, partitioning, consumer groups │
  ├───────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ Cost                      │ Storage cost only; compute on trigger                    │ Kafka cluster + compute continuously running               │
  ├───────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ Volume scale              │ Good up to ~millions files/day                           │ Better for billions of events/day continuous               │
  ├───────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ Intermittent connectivity │ Ideal — Pi buffers locally, uploads when connected       │ Requires persistent connection or local Kafka broker       │
  └───────────────────────────┴──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┴────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  Recommendation for E-Fence: Auto Loader is the correct default.

  The Raspberry Pi is a field-deployed intermittent edge device. It should buffer observations locally (SQLite, JSON files, or a local queue) and upload batches when network
  connectivity is available. Auto Loader handles file arrival natively, with no infrastructure beyond a writable cloud volume. Replayability is perfect — the raw files are the
  source of truth.

  Kafka becomes appropriate if:
  - Sub-second latency is required for real-time alerting (< 5 second response to intrusion)
  - Sensor density exceeds 50+ sensors generating >100K events/minute continuously
  - A managed Kafka service (Confluent Cloud, Azure Event Hubs) is already in the stack

  Hybrid pattern for low-latency alerting: Use Auto Loader for bronze/silver archival, and a lightweight MQTT → Databricks Structured Streaming path for real-time gold alert
  triggers only. This avoids the full Kafka operational burden while achieving sub-second alert latency on the critical path.

