  The hash salt is stored in Databricks Secrets scope efence-secrets, key mac-hash-salt. It is injected into the pipeline as a Spark config value using the {{secrets/scope/key}}
  substitution in the pipeline JSON configuration. The salt is never stored in code, config files, or notebooks.

  For law enforcement / authorized de-anonymization requests: the mapping table is maintained as a separate, access-controlled Delta table that must be populated explicitly by an
  authorized process — it is not automatically populated by the pipeline.

