  7. Correlation and Analytics Design

  Why Wi-Fi and BT stay separate through silver

  - Different event frequencies (Wi-Fi: beacons ~10/sec per AP; BLE: advertisements 1–50/sec per device)
  - Different identifier semantics (BSSID is an AP identifier; BLE address may be IRK-derived)
  - Different dedup windows (Wi-Fi: 2h; BLE: 1h)
  - Separate bronze schemas allow protocol-specific schema evolution without coupling
  - Access control can differ per protocol

  Gold correlation patterns implemented

  1. Device Timeline (efence.gold.device_timeline)
  Union of all observations with protocol tag and unified device_id_hash. Enables:
  - Full movement history per hashed device ID
  - Protocol-agnostic frequency analysis (how often is a device seen?)
  - Time-series features for ML models

  2. Co-presence Events (efence.gold.copresence_events)
  Stream-stream window join: same sensor_id, within ±30 seconds. Enables:
  - Cross-protocol entity resolution: one physical device with both Wi-Fi and BT radios
  - Build candidate entity clusters: wifi_device_hash ↔ bt_device_hash linkage graph
  - copresence_score drives confidence weighting

  3. Perimeter Alerts (efence.gold.perimeter_alerts)
  Rule-based scoring on:
  - rssi_dbm >= -65 (device within ~10–15m of sensor)
  - confidence >= 0.7
  - Randomized/unknown identifier flag
  - No prior sighting history (novel device)
  - threat_score 0.0–1.0 composite

  Additional correlation patterns (design, not yet implemented)

  Repeated visitor analysis:
  SELECT device_id_hash, protocol, sensor_id,
         COUNT(*) as sighting_count,
         MIN(event_time) as first_seen, MAX(event_time) as last_seen,
         DATEDIFF(MAX(event_date), MIN(event_date)) as days_active
  FROM efence.gold.device_timeline
  GROUP BY device_id_hash, protocol, sensor_id
  HAVING sighting_count > 5
  ORDER BY sighting_count DESC;

  Directional movement (multi-sensor):
  -- RSSI gradient across sensors for same device in a time window
  SELECT device_id_hash, window_start,
         COLLECT_LIST(STRUCT(sensor_id, rssi_dbm, latitude, longitude)) as sensor_readings
  FROM efence.gold.device_timeline
  WHERE event_time BETWEEN :start AND :end
  GROUP BY device_id_hash, window(event_time, '30 seconds')
  HAVING SIZE(sensor_readings) > 1;

  Unknown device scoring (ML-ready feature set):
  - sighting_count_24h — frequency of sightings in last 24h
  - first_seen_ever — is this device_id_hash new?
  - max_rssi_ever — has this device ever been close?
  - copresence_count — how many times correlated with BT/Wi-Fi?
  - randomized_address — identity obfuscation flag
  - unique_sensor_count — how many sensors have seen this device?

